<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (EC) No 2722/95 of 24 November 1995 on special conditions for the granting of private storage aid for pigmeat </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 2722/95 sealiha eraladustusabi andmise eritingimuste kohta 24. november 1995 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 2759/75 of 29 October 1975 on the common organization of the market in pigmeat (1), as last amended by the Act of Accession of Austria, Finland and Sweden and by Regulation (EC) No 3290/94 (2), and in particular Articles 4 (6) and 5 (4) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 29. oktoobri 1975. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 2759/75 sealihaturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, (1) viimati muudetud Austria, Soome ja Rootsi &uuml;hinemisaktiga ning m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 3290/94, (2) eriti selle artikli 4 l&otilde;iget 6 ja artikli 5 l&otilde;iget 4, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas intervention measures may be taken in respect of pigmeat if, on the representative markets of the Community, the average price for pig carcases is less than 103 % of the basic price and is likely to remain below that level; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: sealiha puhul v&otilde;ib v&otilde;tta sekkumismeetmeid juhul, kui &uuml;henduse t&uuml;&uuml;pilistel turgudel on sear&uuml;mpade keskmine hind madalam kui 103% baashinnast ning t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt j&auml;&auml;b sellest madalamaks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the market situation has been characterized by a marked fall in prices below the level mentioned; whereas, in view of seasonal and cyclical trends, this situation could persist; </inglise>
<eesti> turuolukorda iseloomustab hindade m&auml;rgatav langus nimetatud tasemest madalamale; hooajalisi ja ts&uuml;klilisi suundumusi silmas pidades v&otilde;ib selline olukord olla p&uuml;siv; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas intervention measures must be taken; whereas these can be limited to the granting of private storage aid; </inglise>
<eesti> tuleb v&otilde;tta sekkumismeetmed; k&otilde;nealused meetmed v&otilde;ivad piirduda eraladustusabi andmisega; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 3 of Council Regulation (EEC) No 2763/75 (3) provides for the possibility of curtailing or extending the storage period; whereas, therefore, provision should be made to fix not only the amounts of aid for a specific period of storage but also the amounts to be added or deducted if this period is curtailed or extended; </inglise>
<eesti> n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 2763/75 (3) artikliga 3 n&auml;hakse ette v&otilde;imalus ladustamisaja l&uuml;hendamiseks v&otilde;i pikendamiseks; seet&otilde;ttu tuleks peale konkreetse ladustamisaja jaoks antava abi summa kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata ka k&otilde;nealuse aja l&uuml;hendamise v&otilde;i pikendamise korral liidetavad v&otilde;i mahaarvatavad summad; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in order to facilitate administrative and control work resulting from the conclusion of contracts, minimum quantities should be fixed; </inglise>
<eesti> lepingute s&otilde;lmimisest tuleneva haldus- ja kontrollitegevuse h&otilde;lbustamiseks tuleks kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata miinimumkogused; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the security should be fixed at a level such as will oblige the storer to fulfil the obligations undertaken by him; </inglise>
<eesti> tagatis tuleks kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata nii, et see kohustab ladustajat oma kohustusi t&auml;itma; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures allowing early removal from storage, provided for in Article 9 (4) of Commission Regulation (EEC) No 3444/90 (4), as amended by Regulation (EEC) No 3533/93 (5), should no longer apply in order to ensure equal treatment of all products regardless of their destination; </inglise>
<eesti> tagamaks k&otilde;igi toodete v&otilde;rdset kohtlemist s&otilde;ltumata toodete sihtkohast, ei tohiks enam kohaldada komisjoni m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3444/90 (4) (muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 3533/93 (5)) artikli 9 l&otilde;ikes 4 etten&auml;htud meetmeid, mis lubavad toodete varasemat laost &auml;raviimist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Management Committee for Pigmeat has not delivered an opinion within the time limit set by its chairman, </inglise>
<eesti> sealihaturu korralduskomitee ei ole oma eesistuja m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htaja jooksul arvamust avaldanud, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> As from 27 November 1995 applications for private storage aid may be introduced in accordance with the provisions of Regulation (EEC) No 3444/90. </inglise>
<eesti> Taotlusi eraladustusabi saamiseks v&otilde;ib m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;) nr 3444/90 s&auml;testatud korras esitada alates 27. novembrist 1995. </eesti>
<inglise> The list of products which qualify for aid and the relevant amounts are set out in the Annex hereto. </inglise>
<eesti> Abi saamise tingimustele vastavate toodete loetelu ja asjakohased summad esitatakse k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse lisas. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> If the period of storage is extended or curtailed, the amount of the aid shall be adjusted accordingly. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui ladustamisaega pikendatakse v&otilde;i l&uuml;hendatakse, kohandatakse vastavalt ka abisummat. </eesti>
<inglise> The amounts of the supplements and deductions per month and per day are set out in columns 5 and 6 of the said Annex. </inglise>
<eesti> Liidetavad ja mahaarvatavad summad kuu ja p&auml;eva kohta on s&auml;testatud nimetatud lisa veergudes 5 ja 6. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> The minimum quantities per contract and per product shall be as follows: </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;he lepingu ja &uuml;he toote kohta on miinimumkogused j&auml;rgmised: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) 10 tonnes for boned products; </inglise>
<eesti> a) 10 tonni konditustatud toodete puhul; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) 15 tonnes for all the other products. </inglise>
<eesti> b) 15 tonni k&otilde;igi muude toodete puhul. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> The security shall be 20 % of the amounts of aid set out in the Annex. </inglise>
<eesti> Tagatis on 20% lisas s&auml;testatud abisummadest. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> The contractor cannot remove from storage all or part of the quantity of products under contract as foreseen in Article 9 (4) of Regulation (EEC) No 3444/90. </inglise>
<eesti> Vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3444/90 artikli 9 l&otilde;ikele 4 ei tohi lepingupool laost &auml;ra viia kogu lepinguj&auml;rgset toodete kogust v&otilde;i osa sellest. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the day of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas avaldamise p&auml;eval. K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
